      "id": 1462,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:33",
      "content": "## Task: Fix `synapse update` — no output printed\n\n**Root cause:** In `src/index.ts`, the `update` command calls `synapseInit(resolve(targetPath ?? '.'), true)` — the second argument is `silent=true`, which suppresses all stdout output.\n\n**Fix:** Change that call to `synapseInit(resolve(targetPath ?? '.'), false, true)` — `silent=false`, `update=true`. This matches how `synapseInit` is intended to be called for the update path (see the `isNew`/`update` branch at the bottom of the function that prints `[Synapse] Updated templates and config at …`).\n\nThe `update` command is around line 184–188 in `src/index.ts`.\n\n## Steps\n1. `synapse worktree create developer-33-fix-update-silent`\n2. Edit the one-line fix in `src/index.ts`\n3. `tsc` — verify clean build\n4. Commit and report DONE with SHA",
